  "texts": [
    "The hypergraph representation enables efficient learning and inference with linear time complexity, making it suitable for large-scale datasets.",
    "To further improve performance, the authors adopt a log-linear model similar to conditional random fields for the extraction and classification of entities and optimize this using L-BFGS optimization methods.",
    "The results of the study demonstrate significant improvements in precision and F1 scores over baseline models when evaluated on the ACE2004 and ACE2005 datasets, both of which contain overlapping mentions.",
    "The proposed mention hypergraph model outperformed traditional models, such as conditional random fields (CRF), with an F1 score improvement of up to 2-3% across datasets.",
    "Additionally, the model's scalability was evaluated by increasing the number of possible mention types, showing that it maintained linear time complexity while handling significantly more complex structures than existing models."
  ],
